Interface FloatInputPoll

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    FloatInput
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FloatStatus, PIDControl

    public interface FloatInputPoll
    A FloatInputPoll is a way to get the current state of a float input. By convention, most float inputs and outputs have states that range from -1.0f to 1.0f.

    skeggsc
